dismissalComment.html: Dan the man strikes with a big wicket!  He pushed this one through quicker, Mahela was looking to lift it over the off-side field but missed it completely. Clatter! The off stump is pegged back. it landed on a length on the off and middle line and crashed into the off stump.  Excellent knock but he has to go now. New Zealand move ahead in this fascinating game.

dismissalText.commentary: Nuwan Kulasekara not out 57 (56b 2x4 4x6 94m) SR: 101.78

dismissalComment.html: Dilshan falls after an electrifying cameo. It was the short  lifting delivery that climbs on him and he mistimed the hook straight to deep square-leg. The other day he said, his wife keeps telling him don't hook don't hook and that he says yes but goes to do exactly that! And he has fallen to that shot now. Having said that, that's the shot that fetches him lots and lots of runs. No use shelving that. But but .. you should listen to your wife now and then I say!

commentTextItems.html: And it's all over. Full delivery, dragged straight to mid-on. Fine win for NZ. The group is split wide open. Sri Lanka are virtually out of this tournament. Sorrow and joy collide.

commentPostTextItems.html: Hang on for the post-match quotes from the captains.

Sanga: "At the end of the day we have to look back and see we didnt have enough wickets in hand. Mahela and Kulasekara played superbly. We have to improve our fielding standards. We have to take responsibility at the end of the day for the mistakes."

Vettori: "The way Ryder and McCullum gave us a great start put the dressing room in good shape. We carried the momentum all the way through. IT was a fantastic pitch. Sri Lanka put a lot of pressure on us in the end. Guptill maintained a good composure and played very well. Tuffey has come back from injury and has stood up today. We can go into the game against England, knowing the wicket, knowing what we have to do and we can win that and go to semi-finals." Vettori is also the man of the match.
That's it from us. Thanks for logging. Hop on to the England v South Africa game.
